<question xmlns='http://www.gradians.com'>
  <statement>
    <tex>%text
Evaluate:
%
\qquad \left\vert \begin{array}{cc}
    \cos 15^\circ &amp; \sin 15^\circ \\
    \sin 75^\circ &amp; \cos 75^\circ
  \end{array}\right\vert</tex>
  </statement>
  <step>
    <context>\left\vert \begin{array}{cc}
    \cos 15^\circ &amp; \sin 15^\circ \\
    \sin 75^\circ &amp; \cos 75^\circ
  \end{array}\right\vert \\
%text
What is the correct expansion of the above?
%</context>
    <tex correct='true'>\begin{align}
  {\small\left\vert \begin{array}{cc}
    \cos 15^\circ &amp; \sin 15^\circ \\
    \sin 75^\circ &amp; \cos 75^\circ
  \end{array}\right\vert} 
    &amp;=\cos 15^\circ \cos 75^\circ - \sin 15^\circ\sin 75^\circ  \\
\end{align}</tex>
    <tex>\begin{align}
  {\small\left\vert \begin{array}{cc}
    \cos 15^\circ &amp; \sin 15^\circ \\
    \sin 75^\circ &amp; \cos 75^\circ
  \end{array}\right\vert} 
    &amp;=\cos 15^\circ \cos 75^\circ + \sin 15^\circ\sin 75^\circ  \\
\end{align}</tex>
    <reason>D=\left\vert\begin{array}{cc}
  a &amp; b \\ c &amp; d
\end{array}\right\vert \\
%text
Expansion of a $2\times 2$ determinant of
the form shown above is $D=a\cdot d-b\cdot c$.
Therefore,
%

\begin{align}
  {\small\left\vert \begin{array}{cc}
    \cos 15^\circ &amp; \sin 15^\circ \\
    \sin 75^\circ &amp; \cos 75^\circ
  \end{array}\right\vert} 
    &amp;=\cos 15^\circ \cos 75^\circ - \sin 15^\circ\sin 75^\circ
\end{align}</reason>
  </step>
  <step>
    <context>%text
Can $\cos 15^\circ \cos 75^\circ - \sin 15^\circ\sin 75^\circ$ be
rewritten as below?
%</context>
    <tex correct='true'>\begin{align}
  \cos 15^\circ \cos 75^\circ - \sin 15^\circ\sin 75^\circ
    &amp;=\cos(15^\circ+75^\circ) \\
    &amp;=\cos(90^\circ) \\
    &amp;= 0    
\end{align}
</tex>
    <tex>\begin{align}
  \cos 15^\circ \cos 75^\circ - \sin 15^\circ\sin 75^\circ
    &amp;=\cos(15^\circ-75^\circ) \\
    &amp;=\cos(-60^\circ) \\
    &amp;=\dfrac{1}{2}   
\end{align}
</tex>
    <reason></reason>
  </step>
  <choices>
    <tex>\dfrac{1}{2}</tex>
    <tex correct='true'>0</tex>
    <tex>-\dfrac{1}{2}</tex>
    <tex>1</tex>
  </choices>
</question>